---
title: "Micromanagement in Federally Funded Research in Canada Reaches Unheard Of Lows"
---

A quip from the CBC on a [predicted drop in Federally funded research](http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/story/2013/07/31/science-technology-spending-federal-government.html) in Canada for 2013-2014 comes with a bonus stock photo of Canadian Prime Minister [Stephen Harper](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Harper) visiting a lab.

He's probably just visiting, but in light of [previous complaints of micromanagement](http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/keith-beardsley/message-control-harper_b_1936900.html) by the [PMO](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Office_of_the_Prime_Minister_%28Canada%29), could point to a trend towards doing the same in labs across the country.
